    <div class="record-slider">
        <div class="slider-container">
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="633">
                        <time>26/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>🏷: Student Achievement: Charlotte<br>.<br>📅: 16 March 2026<br>.<br>🖊: Charlotte recently participated in the 78th Hong Kong Schools Music Festival. She was awarded first place in the Graded Piano Solo (Grade 5) category and second place in the Piano Duet (Junior) category.<br>Well done, Charlotte!<br>.<br>💬: #esfbeaconhillschool #beaconhillschoolhk #bhs #bhsig</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/3c17d7f87e4a3ad79f834f338169341c.jpg" alt="652684730_1409416551199529_6205082678235800980_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="632">
                        <time>25/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>🏷: BHS: Student-Led Conference<br>.<br>📅: 19 March 2025<br>.<br>🖊: The Student‑Led Conferences were a celebration of learning across the school. Students led the conversations, explaining their learning with an emphasis on progress rather than simple achievement.<br>They demonstrated a clear understanding of their strengths and challenges and described how they use those strengths to advance their learning. This is learning how to learn - developing the habits and mindset of lifelong learners who value the journey of growth as the foundation for a meaningful life.<br>.<br>💬: #esfbeaconhillschool #beaconhillschoolhk #bhs #bhsig</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/5cb3950504fe446dfc22769015492dbb.jpg" alt="653987844_1410350847772766_5150344897040940342_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="631">
                        <time>24/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>🏷: Student Achievement: Inez<br>.<br>📅: 16 March 2026<br>.<br>🖊: Inez took part in the Global Drawing Contest and won the silver award in the "Flavors of Home" drawing competition.<br>Well done, Inez!<br>.<br>💬: #esfbeaconhillschool #beaconhillschoolhk #bhs #bhsig</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/88e7188ba4109dc59caf786d432a6c45.jpg" alt="651304746_1409415224532995_2122975736646503945_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="630">
                        <time>23/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>🏷: Y6: PYPX<br>.<br>📅: 18 March 2025<br>.<br>🖊: The Year 6 students hosted their PYPX, and as part of Student‑Led Conference day, they welcomed families of Years 1–5 for Community Sharing. Both events were filled with positive energy, thoughtful sharing, and engaging questions.<br>Adults who attended were greatly encouraged by what was heard and observed. The Year 6 students spoke confidently about their enquiries, the progress they have made, and the actions they are taking. They explained their processes, reflected on challenges, and described how feedback helped them improve.<br>.<br>💬: #esfbeaconhillschool #beaconhillschoolhk #bhs #bhsig</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/fa60ba9ff9cd7a90764f22f0fcd6ad2f.jpg" alt="653031894_1410346721106512_3716187730131317748_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="629">
                        <time>22/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>🏷: Student Achievement: Wallace<br>.<br>📅: 17 March 2026<br>.<br>🖊: Wallace joined his mum’s company volunteer team in early March to visit elderly residents of Kwong Fuk Estate, next to Wang Fuk Court in Tai Po, where recovery after the recent fire is still difficult, and many feel anxious. Together with the volunteers, Wallace helped distribute warm CNY goodie bags and spent time chatting with residents, offering comfort and assessing their needs. Their visit helped ease fears and enabled the Tsung Tsin Mission of Hong Kong Social Service -  Fuk Hong Neighbourhood Elderly Centre to provide timely support.<br>Keep it up, Wallace!<br>.<br>💬: #esfbeaconhillschool #beaconhillschoolhk #bhs #bhsig</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/8438284326b40335ca9b86361a3d0533.jpg" alt="651757649_1409472064527311_5600509022869417471_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="628">
                        <time>21/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>🏷: Student Achievement: Isabelle<br>.<br>📅: 10 March 2026<br>.<br>🖊: Isabelle took part in her Jazz exam and achieved Honours with Distinction. She loves Jazz dance and works very hard in her practice. Recently, she performed two dances at the AIA Carnival and had a great time.<br>Well done, Isabelle!<br>.<br>💬: #esfbeaconhillschool #beaconhillschoolhk #bhs #bhsig</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/0a656a2ddd20d102dccb4f7d453b2ece.jpg" alt="649266631_1402859331855251_7488740880761020089_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="627">
                        <time>20/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>🏷: Basketball Club: HKPSSA Kowloon Basketball Championship<br>.<br>📅: 12 February 2026<br>.<br>🖊: The girls' team excelled throughout the tournament and were crowned champions in a thrilling 10-8 victory against AISHK. This was the only game where a basket was scored against them, which highlighted how strong they were on defence. This was the girls' best result ever, having previously finished 2nd and 3rd.<br>.<br>💬: #esfbeaconhillschool #beaconhillschoolhk #bhs #bhsig</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/ed5df07ec3685c20f17b7095083b89af.jpg" alt="655009494_18096065684066704_541956377241357902_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="626">
                        <time>20/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>🏷: Tag Rugby Club: HKPSSA Tag Rugby Championships<br>.<br>📅: 16 March 2025<br>.<br>🖊: It was an action-packed day of sport as both the Boys and Girls Tag Rugby teams competed in the HKPSSA Tag Rugby Championships. Both squads displayed excellent rugby and immense spirit throughout the tournament, and while we were unlucky that some results did not go our way, the quality of play was outstanding. The boys showcased strong attacking rugby and excellent support play, while the girls excelled in their passing and communication, scoring spectacular tries. A major highlight for the boys was successfully retaining the Lion Rock in their match against Shatin Junior, while the girls showed incredible grit by coming back from two tries down to draw against a strong Harrow team. Congratulations to Klaus and Tia, who were selected by their peers as the Most Valuable Players.<br>.<br>💬: #esfbeaconhillschool #beaconhillschoolhk #bhs #bhsig</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/efcb1b068a66219a99fe57bf7c81f636.jpg" alt="651883726_1410343127773538_6769161130775954511_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="625">
                        <time>19/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>🏷: Student Achievement: Navya<br>.<br>📅: 7 March 2026<br>.<br>🖊: Navya participated in the Kowloon Cricket Club Match Play Series for 6–8-year-olds, where she emerged as the top player and won the gold medal.<br>Well done, Navya!<br>.<br>💬: #esfbeaconhillschool #beaconhillschoolhk #bhs #bhsig</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/c0300b89b8423c356dac0bd4cddfa6a1.jpg" alt="649092974_1401949361946248_7740065389139299592_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="624">
                        <time>18/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>🏷: BHS: BHS School Fair..See You There!<br>.<br>📅: 13 March 2026<br>.<br>🖊: Get ready for an unforgettable evening at our School Fair on 𝗙𝗿𝗶𝗱𝗮𝘆, 𝟮𝟬 𝗠𝗮𝗿𝗰𝗵 | 𝟱–𝟴 𝗣𝗠!<br><br>💫 𝗛𝗶𝗴𝗵𝗹𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁𝘀:<br><br>🖼️ 𝙎𝙞𝙡𝙚𝙣𝙩 𝘼𝙪𝙘𝙩𝙞𝙤𝙣 — Support our Artist-in-Residence Project and bid for your child’s class artwork!<br>🎶 𝙇𝙞𝙫𝙚 𝙋𝙚𝙧𝙛𝙤𝙧𝙢𝙖𝙣𝙘𝙚𝙨 — Enjoy music by our talented students and friends from ESF Schools.<br>🍿 𝙁𝙤𝙤𝙙 & 𝙁𝙪𝙣 — Delicious bites, bounce castles, pre-loved stalls, popcorn, cotton candy & more!<br><br>🎟️ 𝗧𝗶𝗰𝗸𝗲𝘁𝘀 & 𝗢𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗿𝘀:<br><br>🐦 𝙀𝙖𝙧𝙡𝙮 𝘽𝙞𝙧𝙙 — $25 (more details next week)<br>🎫 𝙍𝙚𝙜𝙪𝙡𝙖𝙧 — $30 on event day | Kids under 3 enter free!<br>🎟️ 𝘾𝙤𝙪𝙥𝙤𝙣𝙨 — 10 for $100 (buy early!)<br><br>🌿 To promote sustainable living among our students, please bring or use reusable plates and cutlery. Thank you for supporting our green initiatives! ♻️<br><br>🚐 We’ve got you covered with a free shuttle bus from Kowloon Tong MTR — schedule coming soon. Stay tuned!<br><br>Mark your calendars and join us for a night full of fun, food, and community spirit! 💙<br>.<br>💬: #esfbeaconhillschool #beaconhillschoolhk #bhs #bhsig</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
